title: 'N/A'
body: 'The Bosch LT-BOXX 170 and 272 are a nice addition to my older L-BOXX. They feel well made and are quite sturdy
column5: though both arrived with a few scratches on them (if only Bosch would wrap them in something) and the first LT-BOXX 170 had a floppy handle that turned out to be a fault
column6: not a design flaw as I originally thought.  Unfortunately
column7: the new style inlay trays don’t fit inside the LT-BOXX 170 unless you trim them down at the left or right hand side. None of the inlays would fit in the LT-BOXX 272.  Incidentally
column8: the LT-BOXX 170 and 272 are Made in Germany
column10: and not in Poland or Slovakia like the new style L-BOXX’s.'
